# isEqual(to:)

**Instance Method**

Returns a Boolean value indicating whether this data object is the same as another.

## Declaration

```swift
func isEqual(to other: Data) -> Bool
```

## Parameters

- **other**: The data object with which to compare the receiver.

## Return Value

[doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/Swift/true] if the contents of `otherData` are equal to the contents of the receiver, otherwise [doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/Swift/false].

## Discussion

Two data objects are equal if they hold the same number of bytes, and if the bytes at the same position in the objects are the same.

## Testing Data

- **length**: The number of bytes contained by the data object.
